🧮 NumPy Main Project
A hands-on project built using NumPy, focusing on numerical operations, data analysis, and array manipulations in Python.
This notebook demonstrates how NumPy can simplify complex mathematical and data processing tasks efficiently.

🎯 Objectives
The main objectives of this project are to:
1.Understand the fundamentals of NumPy arrays and their advantages over Python lists.
2.Learn array creation, indexing, slicing, and reshaping operations.
3.Perform mathematical, statistical, and logical computations using NumPy functions.
4.Apply NumPy to simple real-world data analysis scenarios.

🚀 Features
1.Create and manipulate NumPy arrays
2.Perform mathematical and statistical calculations
3.Explore slicing, indexing, and reshaping arrays
4.Demonstrate broadcasting and vectorization
5.Compare NumPy arrays with Python lists in terms of speed and memory
6.Use NumPy for small data analysis examples

🚀 Getting Started Prerequisites 
Python 3.8+ 
Jupyter Notebook or JupyterLab 
NumPy library

Installation: 
1.Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/poojivelu/numpy-main-project.git 
cd numpy-main-project

2.Install dependencies: pip install numpy jupyter
Running the Notebook 
Option 1: Jupyter Notebook jupyter notebook numpy-main-project.ipynb
Option 2: JupyterLab jupyter lab numpy-main-project.ipynb
Option 3: Google Colab 1.Upload the .ipynb file to Google Drive 2.Open with Google Colab 3.Run all cells (Runtime → Run all)
Option 4: VS Code 1.Install Python and Jupyter extensions 2.Open the .ipynb file 3.Select Python kernel and run cells

📁 Project Structure:
 numpy-major/ │ 
├── numpy-main-project.ipynb # Main Jupyter notebook 
